WHAT IS THIS FILE
The certified computing profile for MediaTek’s Dimensity 9500 flagship
mobile SoC. It defines the Arm C1‑Ultra “Blackhawk” CPU cluster (custom
implementation of Arm v9.2), the 12‑core Mali G1‑Ultra GPU, the NPU 990
AI accelerator (~100 TOPS), the Imagiq 1190 ISP, and the LPDDR5x memory
subsystem. Every subsystem is expressed through auditable formulas.

WHY IT EXISTS
The Dimensity 9500 is the first mobile SoC to break the 4.2 GHz clock
barrier using a custom “C1” implementation of the Cortex‑X925. Its
26 MB combined cache (16 MB L3 + 10 MB SLC) and ~100 TOPS NPU make
it a primary compute target for GIOP on‑device AI grading, text‑to‑LUT
generation, and real‑time HDR fusion. GIOP must model these resources
as formulas to predict processing latency and thermal behaviour.

HOW IT WORKS
CPU Frequency Scaling (C1‑Ultra):
  Perf(f) = Perf_base * (f / f_base)^α
  where α ≈ 0.85 (sub‑linear due to memory wall), f_base = 2.7 GHz,
  f_max = 4.21 GHz (C1‑Ultra). Perf_base = 1.0. Single‑core Geekbench 6
  ≈ 3 600 at 4.21 GHz.

CPU Multi‑Core Throughput (Amdahl):
  P(N) = 1 / ((1 – f_parallel) + f_parallel / N)
  where f_parallel = 0.91, N = 8 (1×C1‑Ultra + 3×C1‑Premium + 4×C1‑Pro).
  Measured multi‑core Geekbench 6 ≈ 12 500.

CPU Cache Hierarchy:
  C1‑Ultra: 2 MB private L2 → hit rate ≈ 0.94
  C1‑Premium: 1 MB private L2 → hit rate ≈ 0.89
  C1‑Pro: 512 KB private L2 → hit rate ≈ 0.82
  16 MB shared L3 + 10 MB SLC → effective L3 miss rate < 2%.
  Effective access time = hit_L2 * 18 + miss_L2 * (hit_L3 * 50 +
  miss_L3 * 250) cycles.

CPU Dynamic Power:
  P_cpu = C_eff * V^2 * f
  where C_eff ≈ 2.6 nF (C1‑Ultra, 3 nm N3P), V = 0.60–1.00 V,
  f = 2.70–4.21 GHz. Sustained TDP: 6 W (smartphone passive cooling).

GPU Throughput (Mali G1‑Ultra, 12 cores):
  FP32 TFLOPS:
    TFLOPS_FP32 = (cores * ALUs_per_core * 2 * f_gpu) / 1e12
    = (12 * 128 * 2 * 1.1e9) / 1e12 ≈ 3.4 TFLOPS
  FP16 TFLOPS:
    TFLOPS_FP16 = 2 * TFLOPS_FP32 ≈ 6.8 TFLOPS
  Ray Tracing: hardware RT cores deliver 2.4 Giga‑rays/s.
  Efficiency: +42% perf/W over Immortalis‑G925.

NPU 990 AI Throughput:
  INT8 TOPS:
    TOPS_INT8 = (MAC_units * 2 * f_npu) / 1e12
    ≈ (24 576 * 2 * 2.0e9) / 1e12 ≈ 98 TOPS (~100 TOPS marketed).
  INT4 TOPS:
    TOPS_INT4 = 2 * TOPS_INT8 ≈ 196 TOPS.
  Stable Diffusion (512×512, 20 steps):
    t_gen = (Total_FLOPs / TOPS_INT8) + memory_latency
    ≈ (2.8e11 / 98e9) + 0.3 s ≈ 2.9 s + 0.3 s ≈ 3.2 s (first pass).
  Subsequent passes benefit from cached U‑Net: ~1.2 s.
  Agentic AI: real‑time LMT suggestion, text‑to‑LUT generation, on‑device
  auto‑grade via transformer decoder.

ISP Imagiq 1190 Throughput:
  Pixel Rate:
    R_isp = f_isp * pixels_per_cycle
    = 1.2e9 * 16 = 19.2 Gpix/s
  Supports 200 MP single‑shot, 4K 60 fps portrait video with continuous
  AF tracking. 18‑bit internal pipeline for HDR fusion.

Memory Bandwidth (LPDDR5x‑10667, 64‑bit):
  BW = bus_width_bytes * f_data * 2(DDR)
  = 8 * 10.667e9 * 2 = 170.7 GB/s
  For 200 MP RAW (16‑bit): frame size ≈ 400 MB; transfer time ≈ 2.3 ms.

